{
  format: 1
  name: resource-path-identifies-no-entry-rejected
  suite: static
  spec: ["#package-structure", "#loading"]
  tags: ["tampering"]
  note: '''
    Stripped-entry tampering, distinct from the digest-mismatch and
    path-traversal cases: the $resources path is well-formed and stays inside
    the archive root, its digest is well-formed, but the named archive entry is
    simply not present (as if removed after the definition was authored, so no
    bytes exist to digest). §4.1: "Paths MUST remain inside the archive root and
    MUST identify one entry"; §9.2 step 2: "verify the artifact entries and
    resource digests". The resolution of the referenced entry fails during
    complete validation, so the load is rejected before activation and no
    surface ever becomes reachable. No `resources` member is declared, so the
    path resolves to nothing (see NOTES.md).
  '''

  package: {
    "$liasse": 1
    "$app": "t.missingentry@1.0.0"
    "$resources": {
      "logo": {
        "$path": "resources/logo.txt"
        "$media": "text/plain"
        "$sha256": "e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855"
      }
    }
    "$model": {
      "items": {
        "$key": "id"
        "id": "text"
      }
    }
  }

  expect: {
    outcome: invalid
    violates: ["#package-structure", "#loading"]
    detail: "resource path 'resources/logo.txt' identifies no archive entry"
  }
}
